<item>
            <title>[SPARK-32529] Spark 3.0 History Server May Never Finish One Round Log Dir Scan</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32529</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If there are a large number (&amp;gt;100k) of applications log dir, listing the log dir will take a few seconds. After getting the path list some applications might have finished already, and the filename will change from &quot;foo.inprogress&quot; to &quot;foo&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It leads to a problem when adding an entry to the listing, querying file status like `fileSizeForLastIndex` will throw out a `FileNotFoundException` exception if the application was finished. And the exception will abort current loop, in a busy cluster, it will make history server couldn&apos;t list and load any application log.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
